    "#This code was used to create figures 2b-2e. \n",
    "#Here, we put random noise with different magnitudes at the parameter of the Jacobian of a second-order model, starting from\n",
    "#the optimal homogeneous parameter configuration.\n",
    "#We calculate the best improvement in relation to the optimal homogeneous, and the fraction of noises that lead to an improvement. This \n",
    "#allows us to understand how each different network is susceptible to having disorder promoted stability."
   ]
  },
